<title type="html"><![CDATA[7/19 (Thur.) 4 Best Things to Do in your Free Time/ How to persuade people? (Host: Morris)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=189&amp;p=203#p203"><![CDATA[
<span style="font-weight: bold">Session I: 4 Best Things to Do in your Free Time</span><br /><br />Please watch the video, and join the meeting to share you ideas and practise English.<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d9W2GO1LhP4">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d9W2GO1LhP4</a><!-- m --><br /><br />According to the video, the four best things to do when we are bored are:<br />1.Exercise<br />2.Reading<br />3.Meditation<br />4.Hobby/Passion<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Questions:</span><br />1.If you watched the videos, please summarize what you have learned and share it with other table members. What are the four best things to do when you are bored? Which one is the most helpful to you?  <br />2.How much free time do you usually have on a working day and on a holiday, respectively?  How do you spend it?  Do you think you live a busy life or a lazy one?  Do or will you do any things mentioned in the video?<br />3.Besides the four things mentioned in the video, what are other things we can do to enrich our lives? <br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session II: How to persuade people?</span><br /><br />Please watch the video, and join the meeting to share you idears and practise English.<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xmkfg_dcHFI">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xmkfg_dcHFI</a><!-- m --><br /><br />According to the video, the six tips/secrets to persuade others are:<br />1.Reciprocity<br />2.Scarcity<br />3.Authority<br />4.Consistency<br />5.Linking<br />6.Consensus<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Questions:</span><br />1.If you watched the videos, please summarize what you have learned and share it with other table members. What are the six tips to persuade people? Which one impresses you the most?<br />2.Have you used any of the tips or seen anyone using any of them to persuade you before? Were the tips useful? <br />3.Have you bought anything on TV shopping channels before?  Do you think that the TV hosts are good at persuading the audience to buy their products?  Which kind of tips do they usually use?  <br />4.If you want to persuade your friends to attend Royal English Club, which tips can be used? Why?? <br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Agenda</span><br />7:00-7:25 Greetings and free talk<br />7:25-7:30 Opening remarks/ Newcomers self-introduction/ Grouping<br />(Session I)<br />7:30 ~ 8:10pm discussion session (40 mins)<br />8:10 ~ 8:25pm summarization (15 mins)<br />8:25 ~ 8:30pm Regrouping<br />(Session II)<br />8:30 ~9:10pm discussion session (40 mins)<br />9:10 ~9:25pm summarization (15 mins)<br />9:25 ~9:30pm Concluding remarks/feedback from newcomers<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">The meeting place of Thursday:</span><br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第一區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=827">Jason Tang</a> — Sat Jul 14, 2018 1:54 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
